Usage:
    rails generate rails_show NAME

Description:
    Generates a controller, view, and test for displaying this app's code. Put a name after rails_show to name the controller and route. If no name is provided, it'll use "sources"

Example:
    rails generate rails_show code

    This will create:
        Controller: app/controllers/codes_controller.rb
        Test: test/controllers/codes_controller_test.rb
        Views: app/views/codes/show.html.erb